  "local_port": 45428,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get call history for my Airtel prepaid number?",
  "response": "Accessing your Airtel prepaid call history can be done through several convenient methods. Below are the most common ways to retrieve your call logs:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Airtel Thanks App**\n\nThe **Airtel Thanks App** is a comprehensive tool provided by Airtel to manage your account easily.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Download the App:**\n   - **Android:** [Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.airtel.thanks)\n   - **iOS:** [Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/in/app/airtel-thanks/id1125806840)\n   \n2. **Log In:**\n   - Open the app and log in using your Airtel prepaid number.\n   - Enter the OTP (One-Time Password) sent to your mobile number for verification.\n\n3. **Navigate to Call History:**\n   - Once logged in, tap on **\"My Account\"** or **\"Usage\"**.\n   - Here, you can view detailed call history, including incoming, outgoing, and missed calls.\n\n---\n\n### **2. USSD Codes**\n\nUSSD codes provide a quick way to access your account details without the need for internet connectivity.\n\n**Common USSD Codes:**\n- **Check Account Balance and Details:**\n  - Dial `*121#` and press the call button.\n  - Follow the on-screen prompts to navigate to your call history.\n\n- **Specific Call History Codes:**\n  - **Note:** USSD codes can vary by region. If `*121#` doesn't provide the desired information, check Airtel\u2019s official website or contact customer support for the correct code in your area.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Sending an SMS**\n\nIn some regions, Airtel allows customers to request account details via SMS.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Compose an SMS:**\n   - Type the keyword (e.g., `BAL` for balance), though the exact keyword for call history may vary.\n   \n2. **Send to Airtel Number:**\n   - Send the SMS to a designated Airtel service number (usually `121`).\n\n3. **Receive Details:**\n   - You\u2019ll receive an SMS with your account details, which may include recent call history.\n\n**Note:** Availability and specific keywords can differ based on your location. Verify with Airtel customer service if unsure.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Airtel Customer Care**\n\nIf online methods aren\u2019t suitable, you can directly contact Airtel's customer support for assistance.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Dial Customer Care:**\n   - From your Airtel prepaid number, dial `121`.\n\n2. **Navigate the Menu:**\n   - Follow the voice prompts to reach the option for querying call history.\n\n3. **Request Assistance:**\n   - You might need to verify your identity by providing your mobile number and other relevant details.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Airtel Web Portal**\n\nAccessing your call history via the Airtel website is another reliable method.\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Visit the Official Website:**\n   - Go to [Airtel's Official Website](https://www.airtel.in/) (ensure you're on the correct site based on your country).\n\n2. **Log In:**\n   - Enter your Airtel prepaid number and password to access your account.\n\n3. **Access Call History:**\n   - Navigate to the **\"My Account\"** or **\"Usage Details\"** section to view your call logs.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Visiting an Airtel Store**\n\nIf you prefer in-person assistance or face issues with the above methods:\n\n**Steps:**\n1. **Locate a Nearby Store:**\n   - Use Airtel\u2019s store locator on their official website to find the nearest outlet.\n\n2. **Bring Identification:**\n   - Carry a valid ID and your Airtel prepaid number.\n\n3. **Request Call History:**\n   - Speak with a representative who can assist you in retrieving your call logs.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Considerations**\n\n- **Data Availability:** Typically, call history is available for the past 30 days. For older records, you may need to contact customer support.\n  \n- **Privacy and Security:** Always ensure you\u2019re accessing your information through official Airtel channels to protect your personal data.\n  \n- **Regional Differences:** Services and available methods may vary based on your country. It\u2019s advisable to check Airtel\u2019s official website or contact customer support for region-specific information.\n\n---\n\nBy following the methods outlined above, you should be able to access your Airtel prepaid call history with ease. If you encounter any issues, contacting Airtel customer support directly is the best course of action.",
